<br />
Because the fingerprint of a pass code is stored in cookies.
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">It is a REGISTERED FORUM MEMBER, yet even though the question was asked/answered during registration, it is asked yet again. This is annoying.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />
All the security measures have drawbacks. Most people don't delete cookies, therefore this feature doesn't affect them.
<br />

<br />
